  "server": {
    "name": "io.nyc.nycha",
    "title": "NYC Housing Authority (NYCHA)",
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "description": "Agent-native access to the New York City Housing Authority \u2014 public housing developments, residential addresses, community facilities, utility consumption metering, and aggregate resident statistics from NYC Open Data, plus the net-new ability to report and track a maintenance repair (work order) that today lives only in the Siebel Self Service Portal.",
    "instructions": "Use find_developments / get_development (and get_development_addresses) to locate public housing developments by borough, program, or council district and drill into their buildings. find_facilities covers community facilities, senior/day-care centers, and customer contact centers. find_utility_consumption answers energy/water cost-and-consumption questions per development (PropertyMeter). find_resident_statistics returns AGGREGATE demographics only \u2014 NYCHA never exposes individual households. report_repair (net-new) creates a maintenance work order; it requires an authenticated resident and mutates state \u2014 confirm the unit, category, and problem with the user before submitting, and set emergency=true for no-heat/hot-water/gas/flooding so it routes to the 24-hour contact center."
  },
